{"type":"message","id":"bde45af3","parentId":"7e62408f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:11:49.374Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kk1rcjkou4to_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001132\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Key insight identified: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action defined: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending actions are:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next action from Phase 1 Advancement is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files I have access to and what would be the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nI should check what pulse logs exist and potentially start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me create a concrete action.\r\n\r\nThe most specific and actionable item right now is to:\r\n1. Check what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me propose implementing the TIC experiment - starting with a script that analyzes the pulse logs for invariants vs variants.\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant elements (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant elements (things that change)\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants across pulse logs to test if causal structure = invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script to analyze pulse logs and measure invariant/variant classification accuracy against the >70% success criterion.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:11:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325509372}}
